Nivell 1¶

Exercici 1¶

Agafa el conjunt de dades que vulguis i realitza un pipeline i un gridsearch aplicant l'algorisme de Random Forest.

El segent dataset prov d'un estudi fet en abelles (Apis mellifera) on s'ha registrar l'activitat de cada individu. Els arxius contenen:

  • alive_bees:the results of the bayesian lifetime model with one row for each bee.
  • bee_daily: This file contains one row per bee per day that she was alive for the focal period.

A continuaci s'exposa el significat de cada variable per tots dos datasets:

  • Unnamed: 0: index column
  • bee_id Unique integer for each bee in the hive.
  • days_alive: Number of bees the bees was determined to be alive. If the individual was still alive at the end of the recording, the number of days from the day she hatched until the end of the recording.
  • death_observed: Boolean indicator whether the death occurred during the recording period.
  • annotated_tagged_date: The date on which the bee hatched (and was tagged). Hatch date of the individual, i.e. the date she was tagged.
  • inferred_death_date: Date of death as determined by a model.
  • date: Date in year-month-day format.
  • age: Bee's age in days. Can be NaN if bee has no associated death_date.
  • network_age, network_age_1 and network_age_2: dimensions of network age which is a espectral descomposition of diffeerent tasks in the hive. It reflects the fraction of time spent in the task-associated areas using CCA (canonical-correlation analysis), but no represent the location in hive (Fig. 1; extracted from Wild et al. 2021).

  • dance_floor: Observed percentage of day spent on dance floor. Can be NaN if bee had no high confidence detections (>0.9) on date. Can be 0 if a bee was only seen outside of the annotated areas.
  • honey_storage: Observed percentage of day spent in honey storage. Can be NaN if bee had no high confidence detections. Can be 0 if a bee was only seen outside of the annotated areas.
  • near_exit: Observed percentage of day spent near exit. Can be NaN if bee had no high confidence detections (>0.9) on date. Can be 0 if a bee was only seen outside of the annotated areas.
  • brood_area_total: Observed percentage of day spent in brood area. Can be NaN if bee had no high confidence detections (>0.9) on date. Can be 0 if a bee was only seen outside of the annotated areas.
  • location_descriptor_count: The number of minutes the bee was seen in one of the location labels during that day. I.e., dance_floor * location_descriptor_count calculates the number of minutes, the bee was seen on the dance floor on the given day.
  • death_date: Date the bee was last seen in the colony in year-month-day format. Can be NaN for individuals that did not die until the end of the recording period.
  • circadian_rhythm: R value of a sine with a period of one day fitted to the velocity data of the individual over three days. Can be NaN if the fit did not converge due to a lack of data points.
  • velocity_peak_time: Phase of the circadian sine fit in hours as an offset to 12:00 UTC. Can be NaN if circadian_rhythm is NaN.
  • velocity_day, velocity_night: Mean velocity of the individual between 09:00-18:00 UTC and 21:00-06:00 UTC, respectively. Can be NaN if no velocity data was available for that interval.
  • days_left: Difference in days between date and death_date. Can be NaN if death_date is NaN.

The inform about the labels come from: https://zenodo.org/record/4438013#.Yp-R2OxBxPY

The data belongs to next work: Wild, B., Dormagen, D.M., Zachariae, A. et al. Social networks predict the life and death of honey bees. Nat Commun 12, 1110 (2021). https://doi.org/10.1038/s41467-021-21212-5

Com s d'esperar bee_id no aporta informaci perqu es l'identificador per a cada abella. Per un altre costat, tant age com network age mostren l'edat per a cada individu, sent la primera cronolgica i la segona en funci de la tasca que duen a terme en l'eixam. Els valors negatius en network age poden ser deguts a que han sigut obtinguts per diferents anlisis com CCA y PCA tal i com s'explica en Wild et al. 2021. Per un altre costat, totes les variables relacionades amb l'edat tenen una distribuci semblant tot i presentar mitjanes molt diferentes. Tot i aix, les distncies entre mnims i mxims no varien gaire entre els network age, sent la variable age qui presenta un rang major.

Les variables dance_floor, honey_storage, near_exit i brood_area_total contenen el tant per cent de temps que ha passat l'abella realitzant una tasca concreta. Sent normal que el mnim sigui 0 y el mxim 1. Com es normal al major part de temps s'inverteix en la zona de cria mentre que en la resta d'activitats es veu ms reduda. Sent aquesta on hi ha una major varincia de les dades, mentre que a la resta aquesta variabilitat en la distribuci s menor. Per un altre costat, location_descriptor_count mostra el temps que passa cada abella en una de les tasques concretes.

circadian_rhythm explica com la velocitat de la abella varia en funci del ritme circadiari a travs d'una funci sinusoidal. Segons les dades obtingudes sembla que mostra gran variabilitat entre els diferents individus.

velocity_peak_time s la velocitat mxima que mostra l'abella coincidint amb el punt mxim del seu ritme circadiari. Mentre que velocity_day i velocity_night s la velocitat mitjana durant el dia i la nit respectivament. En tots tres casos el rang de valors no es gaire ampli tot i mostrar una variana petita.

days_left correspn a la diferncia entre el dia que es va fer el registre i el dia que va morir l'abella.

A ms, l'objectiu d'aquest estudi ser intentar predir el temps que es passen les abelles emmagatzemant mel. Sent aquesta la variable resultant o depenent del model.

Per un altre costat, es decideix tractar cada fila com a individu diferent com a primera aproximaci perqu el que fa una abella a mesura que passen els dies varia suficient com per poder-ho analitzar com si fossin individus diferents.

Tamb s'eliminar la columna date i days_left, ja que no es creu que poguin aportar informaci al model perqu la primera mostra el dia que es van recollir les dades mentre que la segona la distncia en temps entre el dia de la mesura i el dia de la mort. El mateix passa amb death_date i hatch_date

En les mostres anteriors es mostra que la majoria de variables presenten una distribuci normal o semblant a la normal. Per tant, en aquets casos es realitzar la imputaci amb la mitja, mentre que en els casos no normals es far amb la mitjana. Tot i aix, com la mitja s molt sensible als outliers es far servir la mitjana en aquells casos que siguin presents de manera desequilibrada.

from sklearn.pipeline import Pipeline
from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestRegressor
from sklearn.preprocessing import RobustScaler

pipeline1 = Pipeline(steps = [('robustScaler', RobustScaler()),
                             ('forest', RandomForestRegressor(n_estimators = 50, max_depth=10, random_state=42))
                             ])

from sklearn.model_selection import GridSearchCV

parameters = {'forest__criterion':['squared_error', 'absolute_error', 'poisson'],
             #'forest__max_features':['auto','sqrt','log2']
             }

grid.fit(train_x, train_y)

print(grid.best_params_)

from nltk.corpus import stopwords
stopWords = set(stopwords.words('english'))

filter_sent = []
for word in tokens:
    if word not in stopWords:
        filter_sent.append(word)
